Cell.Data: Kaitlin Donohue is currently the Recruitment Coordinator for the College of Arts and Letters (CAL) at Stevens Institute of Technology. She performs outreach to national high school students and assists with marketing efforts for undergraduate programs in Science and Technology Studies, Music & Technology, Visual Arts & Technology, and the Humanities and Social Sciences. Prior to her time at Stevens, Ms. Donohue completed her graduate studies at Georgetown University in Biohazardous Threat Agents and Emerging Infectious Diseases. She subsequently spent time working as a Senior Biosurety Analyst at a Government contractor in the Washington, D.C. area. Kaitlin’s time in this role resulted in opportunities to gain experience in marketing, recruiting, business intelligence, and branding; newfound interests which ultimately led to her current position at Stevens.

Ankit kumar Jawla was born & raised in new delhi, capital of India. He is pursuing master’s of science degree in cloud computing & enterprise at Stevens Institution of Technology, USA . Ankit holds a Bachelor of Technology degree in Electronics and Communication engineering from Rajasthan Technical University, India. He has worked as a Senior Executive Engineer in SIEMENS from April ’11- till Aug ’14. Ankit is having extensive experience and management skills and worked for a hi-tech multinational telecommunication company. Siemens Enterprise Communications, is a global communications software and services company. As a senior engineer he was responsible for managing turn key communications projects & developing new business for the company. He has won achievers award for outstanding contribution towards business growth in the financial years 2011-12 & won a excellent employee of the year award in 2012 -13. Ankit Kumar Jawla has good knowledge of cloud platforms like Amazon Elastic Compute Cloud (EC2), Amazon S3, Salesforce. He is working on a cloud based enterprise application using IDE tools & languages like Eclipse, Java, XML etc. Prior to joining Siemens Ankit has also worked in Realvia as Management Trainee. Further, He has under went 4 weeks summer training with PRICOL Ltd, India where he studied about quality control test on two wheeler assemblies of clusters. In under graduation, He won chess competition at TechBloom-2009 (National Level Fest) Rajasthan, India. Ankit represented college as part of chess team and cricket team from 2006-2010. He has a certification of “Basic Concept in Multimedia” from Delhi institution of computer education.Currently He lives in Jersey city, USA. Ankit has lived in India and he speaks 3 languages (English , Hindi & Punjabi) and in his spare time, he really enjoys playing chess & football.

Name: Prasad Sonawane Bio Prasad Sonawane is a current MBA – Marketing student at Stevens Institute of Technology. This is his second Masters Degree from Stevens and the first being in Business Administration and Management. He did his Bachelors in Pharmacy from Pune University in India. He has held various leadership positions throughout his student life, the latest being President of the Graduate Student Council at Stevens, where he manages 22 associations and a healthy budget of $110,000 for all 4,000 graduate students on campus. He has professional experience ranging from working for start-ups to Fortune 100 companies and reporting directly to managers and all the way up to C-suite. He is passionate about leadership and strategy, and his areas of strength include market research, marketing, business development, project management, and consulting. He has headed multiple projects in CPG, Retail, IT, Finance, Banking, and Telecommunications Industries.

Name: Jeston Guy Bio: Jeston is currently employed as a telephony engineer at Verizon Communication. He is responsible for designing telephony networks to deliver high bandwidth circuits mostly to commercial customers. To provision these circuits he will often have to deploy a multiplexer if one is not currently available. His extended duties also include building out the FiOS network and sometimes the copper network to residential and commercial customers. His educational background includes a bachelor of engineering and a master’s in business administration.

Name: Subramanian Vellaiyan Bio: Subramanian Vellaiyan is a graduate student at Stevens Institute of technology pursuing Master’s in Business Intelligence and Analytics. He has a bachelor of engineering in electrical and electronics from Anna University, Chennai. Subramanian has two years of work experience in the field of data loading, business intelligence and big data. His experience was related to retail domain especially in pricing insights and retail promotions of retailers and manufacturers. He has presented a paper on efficient solar cells at PSG College of Technology during his under graduation. Subramanian’s strong foundation in Math’s and Science brought him great accolades from all his teachers back in school. He is very flexible when it comes to new technologies. His technical interest lies primarily in mathematics, quantitative aptitude and anything related to data. Also he is very much interested in setting his future career in the fraud analytics, criminal investigation, etc. Apart from technical activities, Subramanian is passionate about adventure, archaeology, world history, early human inventions, human psychology, astrology and mythological stories.

Paul Svenson is currently a Master of Science candidate in Business Intelligence and Analytics within the Howe School of Technology Management at Stevens Institute of Technology. In addition to taking courses for his degree requirements, Paul works as a Graduate Student Assistant with Stevens Offices of Graduate Admissions, guiding students through the Graduate application process. In his free time, Paul practices and bowls in tournaments with the Stevens Bowling Team, in addition to bowling in two leagues at Bowl-Rite Lanes in Union City, NJ. Paul is a Bachelor of Science in Meteorology with a concentration in Weather Risk Management and holds minors in Mathematics and Statistics. He graduated from Penn State University – University Park Campus in May 2014, receiving honors and recognition for his outstanding achievement in scholarship, experiential learning, and service to his college. During the summer of 2013, Paul worked with NOAA, a branch of the Department of Commerce, conducting research to help increase the efficiency of wind power production from wind turbines throughout the Midwestern United States. Paul presented his findings in Washington D.C. to policy makers and leaders within NOAA. Paul hopes to one day use his diverse background to help organizations solve complex business problems as they relate to a changing and unpredictable weather and climate system.

Name: Yilin Wei Bio: Yilin Wei is a graduate student of M.S. Business Intelligence and Analytics in Stevens Institute of Technology. Nikunj Mathur is originally from India and is currently in a Master’s Program in Enterprise and Cloud Computing at Stevens Institute of Technology. Before coming to Stevens he completed graduation program: B.Tech in Computer Science from Uttar Pradesh Technical University, India in 2011. He is interested in innovation and technology, and is excited by the way technology has evolved to the point that many of our practices and methods around work could change radically. Between 2011-2014, Nikunj worked as a Senior System Executive for the Cognizant Technology Solutions, India. During his tenure at CTS, Nikunj have worked for three different clients and drove the transition process for one of the client. He did intern in SAP from Gas Authority India limited (GAIL) and learnt the ways to extract meaningful information from bulk of data. He worked with charitable trust ‘Lok Kalyan Trust’ to move all their reporting, financials and student and website data to a local server, which has helped them to improve data administration and organize data for easy reporting. Nikunj is interested in the ways cloud computing save money with pay-as-you-go model and looking for the ways a small business could adapt cloud computing.

Name: Yida (Eddy) Wang Bio: Yida Wang is a Master Candidate at Stevens Institute of Technology, program of Business Intelligence and Analytics. He has a bachelor of engineering from Shandong University of Technology. Yida's research is focused on “big data” analysis and business intelligence. He has taken courses such as financial decision making, strategic data management, process analytics & optimization, multivariate data analytics, data warehousing & business intelligence, supply chain management, social network analytics and risk management methods & applications. He interested in finding hidden value inside data for effective decision making and business innovation. He also interested in international trading and marketing strategy. Yida had working experience in Fraser Suites Chengdu, and participated in “young talent program” in Citibank Chengdu. Further, he enjoys being a volunteer and a basketball player.

He is involved in other research streams including the role of social media in social movements and leadership in online communities. Hani had worked and consulted on diverse projects including projects involving open innovation, social networks and healthcare IT. Further, he has experience in conducting quantitative and qualitative research projects with two papers under review in ISR & HPT and ten North American conference publications
